Sentencas: In this paper, detailed materials characterization analyses on the interaction between FeOx nanoparticles infiltrated onto a La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM) backbone cathode in a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) are reported.
Titulo: Characterization of Interaction between Fe-Infiltrates and LSM Backbone in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The infiltration process leads to an increase of 3.4% in cell performance.
Titulo: Characterization of Interaction between Fe-Infiltrates and LSM Backbone in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS), scanning electron microscopy (SEM), transmission electron microscopy (TEM) as well as energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDS) and electron energy loss spectroscopy (EELS) are utilized to perform a comprehensive examination of the microstructure and chemical properties at the interface of the infiltrate and backbone materials.
Titulo: Characterization of Interaction between Fe-Infiltrates and LSM Backbone in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Mn from the LSM backbone diffuses into the FeOx infiltrate and forms a Fe-Mn-O spinel.
Titulo: Characterization of Interaction between Fe-Infiltrates and LSM Backbone in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A small amount of Fe also diffuses into the LSM backbone, which could partially be responsible for the enhanced performance of the cell.
Titulo: Characterization of Interaction between Fe-Infiltrates and LSM Backbone in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The valence state of Mn increases from the surface of the Fe-Mn-O particle into bulk LSM, with the highest value being at the interface of the Fe-Mn-O/LSM backbone.
Titulo: Characterization of Interaction between Fe-Infiltrates and LSM Backbone in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Possible mechanisms are discussed for the change in Mn valence state within the LSM phase.
Titulo: Characterization of Interaction between Fe-Infiltrates and LSM Backbone in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Trace amounts of Mn and La are found in the YSZ phase, as a result of interdiffusion between LSM and YSZ.
Titulo: Characterization of Interaction between Fe-Infiltrates and LSM Backbone in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
